dismissalText.commentary: Aamer Yamin c †Mutumbami b Chigumbura 62 (68b 5x4 4x6 78m) SR: 91.17

dismissalComment.html: and there is the wicket. Strangled down leg. What a way to go. Chigumbura does the trick. Not a great ball, short and on leg, Yamin looks to pull but is late on the ball and it kisses the glove and Mutumbami and Chigumbura are ecstatic. Disastrous way to go but end of a fighting, determined innings by Yamin

headshotImage.caption: Bilal Asif player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Bilal Asif player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: and that is the first one! Bilal Asif goes. Very poor shot from him though. The debutant sees the fuller length outside off and goes for the heave down the ground. He can only lob the ball up to mid-off. The bat may have turned in his hands but the ball spoons straight up and Zimbabwe have their first.

headshotImage.caption: Azhar Ali player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Azhar Ali player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: cleans him up. Another one goes. Azhar Ali goes. This one comes back in a touch, may have been the offcutter and Azhar prods at the ball as it takes the inside-edge and then rattles the stumps. Huge wicket. And a great start for Zimbabwe. Pakistan under massive pressure now.

dismissalText.commentary: Asad Shafiq c †Mutumbami b Jongwe 1 (6b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 16.66

dismissalComment.html: another one goes, poor delivery by Jongwe, but he won't care. Asad cannot execute the drive, the ball bounces a touch, takes the edge and the keeper accepts the opportunity with ease. Wide and swinging away from the right-hander and much too full but Shafiq wants to plays the exotic square drive, but he can only feather one through

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez run out (sub [CT Mutombodzi]/†Mutumbami) 27 (41b 5x4 0x6 56m) SR: 65.85

dismissalComment.html: and the pressure has told in the form of a wicket. Fantastic fielding by the substitute. Hafeez flicks again wide of that midwicket fielder and sets off for a run. But the sub dives full-length to his right and makes an amazing stop. Returns a good throw to the keeper and Hafeez is stranded mid-pitch after Malik sends him back. The wicket goes to the fielder there, not much could be done in terms of communication there.

dismissalText.commentary: Sarfaraz Ahmed c Williams b Chibhabha 9 (14b 1x4 0x6 16m) SR: 64.28

dismissalComment.html: Pakistan falling apart at the moment, Sarfraz has popped one straight to extra cover, this length delivery seemed to stop on him as he looked to punch it, hit the bat near the toe end and looped up for a simple catch

dismissalText.commentary: Wahab Riaz run out (Chigumbura) 3 (8b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 37.5

dismissalComment.html: what an effort from Chigumbura. Wahab is walking off. Splendid effort. He makes a run-out of nothing. Wahab's struggle continues as he can only inside-edge a ball back onto his shoe, but he is looking for a single as the ball trickles into the off side. However, Elton is quick on it, and under-arms a throw back onto the stumps as Riaz is sent back - all in one swift motion. Pak are 8 down and EC has his second wicket.

headshotImage.caption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: full toss on middle and Malik chooses to whip the ball to deep square leg for just the one

commentPostTextItems.html: 5.46pm That is it, folks. The match has been called off and Zimbabwe have levelled the series in controversial circumstances. The light has not got any better. Pakistan can be extremely proud of their performance, and Malik even more so. It was a real masterclass in batting under pressure with more than the bowling to worry about. He paced it unbelievably well and it is a shame that we didn't get to see a 100-over match. But, such is cricket and life. Zimbabwe can be extremely happy with the win but they did stumble towards the end under pressure. Initially though, things were entirely different. Zimbabwe bowled tight lines and held onto their catches and some of Pakistan's batsmen threw their wickets away. Nonetheless, nothing should be taken away from the quality of the game and grit from the batsmen from both sides.

Azhar Ali: 'It was a lovely game, Malik and Yamin made us comeback in the game when it looked like a one-sided game. Zimbabwe played really well, we could have retricted them to under 250 but they played well at the end. But we lost too many wickets at the start.
<b>Elton Chigumbura is also the Man of the Match<b>

Elton Chigumbura: 'Obviously, it's a good feeling. The partnership between Chamu and Chari set things up for us. There was lots of pressure for the team and the way we went out today, showed good character. Hopefully, I can carry on with what I did today. I had to keep fighting today.'
5.40pm Doesn't look like we will have more play today. Absolutely tragic this will be for Pakistan after that amazing comeback and one of Malik's best international innings.
Sannan Malik: "That's not fair to Cricket that's simply unacceptable "

Yahya: "Simple solution for such situations: ICC should make a rule that umpires have to inform the players at least one over in advance if they want to call the game off." -- The light just deteriorated and deteriorated, and the umpires did their best to ensure a completed game.

5.35pmMassive pressure for both sides now. The umpires may have called the game off now. Zimbabwe's players are quick to shake hands here. And they trudge off. It is only suspended for the moment. Pakistan are five runs behind the D/L total. Malik has a long chat with the umpires. 5.46 pm is the cut-off time for this light to get any better, which is under 10 minutes.
No Pakistan No. 5 has hit a century in a chase, and Malik is four runs short of that.

headshotImage.caption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: good shot and excellent running by Yasir. Overpitched on middle and off, Malik uppishly drives the ball to long-on who makes a diving stop and returns a good throw but Yasir races back for the second
excellent full delivery, Yasir just about gets bat on it and squirts the ball to short fine leg for one
swiped away in the air, lands just short of the incoming deep midwicket fielder. He returns a wayward throw and they get an overthrow
low full toss on middle, Malik whips the ball to deep square leg and is looking for two but cannot get it

commentPreTextItems.html: 29 off 18. Chigumbura brings himself back. 261 is D/L par at the end of this over, providing no wicket falls

commentTextItems.html: too full on off, Yasir creams another one on the bounce to long-off
another beauty. Malik, take a bow. He gives himself room and carves the ball over point. Amazingly done. Anticipated the length and executed to perfection.

commentPostTextItems.html: FYI, 257 is the D/L par score at the end of the 47th over

headshotImage.caption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022

commentPreTextItems.html: Is there a boundary in this over?

commentTextItems.html: very full again outside off, Yasir drives to cover and goes through for the single. A direct hit would have been out
good delivery again, looking for the yorker. But Yasir converts it into a low full toss and flicks to deep midwicket. Malik runs the first very quickly and comes back for the second
good variation but called wide. Too short maybe. Dug in on off, Yasir gets under it
lovely bowling this by Panyangara. Very full and very wide. Yasir comes down to throw that yorker length off but he misses
excellent yorker once again. Splendid stuff. Yasir can only defend back to the bowler

commentPreTextItems.html: Under 10 RPO required now. But one wicket changes things drastically. Malik is key
hamza: "What an incredible comeback from Pakistan. Never seen anything from 60 for 6 to 240 for 8"

commentTextItems.html: excellent delivery. Yorker on off, dug out to point
high quality shot from Yasir now. Just times a drive past cover for two. Great timing, and the pair get another two.

headshotImage.longCaption: Shoaib Malik player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022

commentTextItems.html: good length now on middle, worked away into the leg side. Malik is looking for two but Raza is quick on it, keeps them down to one

commentPreTextItems.html: Just a reminder, there are no floodlights at this ground

commentTextItems.html: this is getting better and better from Malik.  real masterclass of batting under pressure. Full on off and middle, and Malik opens the face of the bat and hits the ball over the infield to the cover boundary
short and wide again, cut away to third man for a single

commentPreTextItems.html: Some more sawdust coming out. Zimbabwe taking time out of the day, here.

commentTextItems.html: full on leg, clipped to deep square leg for one

commentPreTextItems.html: Right, how will these two play it? For the D/L par-score or normally? I'd suspect they can only look for that boundary an over and hope that the light stays decent. Zimbabwe taking their time though. The umpires take a light-meter reading

commentTextItems.html: unbelievable stuff from Malik. He is in the zone right now, although he gets a gift from the bowler. Short and wide, Malik knows where his gap is and executes perfectly, smashes the ball over point for four

commentPreTextItems.html: The rain seems to have eased a touch, but the light isn't particularly great.

commentTextItems.html: speared in full and quick on middle, Malik drives to long-on for a single.

dismissalComment.html: and that is the first one! Bilal Asif goes. Very poor shot from him though. The debutant sees the fuller length outside off and goes for the heave down the ground. He can only lob the ball up to mid-off. The bat may have turned in his hands but the ball spoons straight up and Zimbabwe have their first.

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Hafeez run out (sub [CT Mutombodzi]/†Mutumbami) 27 (41b 5x4 0x6 56m) SR: 65.85

dismissalComment.html: and the pressure has told in the form of a wicket. Fantastic fielding by the substitute. Hafeez flicks again wide of that midwicket fielder and sets off for a run. But the sub dives full-length to his right and makes an amazing stop. Returns a good throw to the keeper and Hafeez is stranded mid-pitch after Malik sends him back. The wicket goes to the fielder there, not much could be done in terms of communication there.

dismissalComment.html: another one goes, poor delivery by Jongwe, but he won't care. dismissalText.commentary: Aamer Yamin c †Mutumbami b Chigumbura 62 (68b 5x4 4x6 78m) SR: 91.17

dismissalComment.html: and there is the wicket. Strangled down leg. What a way to go. Chigumbura does the trick. Not a great ball, short and on leg, Yamin looks to pull but is late on the ball and it kisses the glove and Mutumbami and Chigumbura are ecstatic. Disastrous way to go but end of a fighting, determined innings by Yamin

dismissalText.commentary: Wahab Riaz run out (Chigumbura) 3 (8b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 37.5

dismissalComment.html: what an effort from Chigumbura. Wahab is walking off. Splendid effort. He makes a run-out of nothing. Wahab's struggle continues as he can only inside-edge a ball back onto his shoe, but he is looking for a single as the ball trickles into the off side. However, Elton is quick on it, and under-arms a throw back onto the stumps as Riaz is sent back - all in one swift motion. Pak are 8 down and EC has his second wicket.
